{{for|other people with this name|Agathocles (disambiguation)}} '''Agathocles''' ({{lang-grc-gre|Ἀγαθοκλῆς}}; fl. 3rd century BC) was a Greek historian who wrote a history of [[Cyzicus]] ({{lang|grc|περὶ Κυζίκου}}) in the [[Ionic Greek|Ionic dialect]].<ref>{{cite book | last = Lesky | first = Albin | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = History of Greek Literature | publisher = [[Hackett Publishing Company]] | year = 1996 | location = [[Indianapolis]] | pages = 624 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=QKiIwZxoH_gC&pg=PA624&dq=agathocles+cyzicus&sig=FtchJ6DrcF-ckFy5DPCvlAPE5iU | doi = | id = | isbn = 0-87220-350-6}}</ref> He is called by [[Athenaeus]] both a [[Babylonia]]n<ref>[[Athenaeus]], i. p. 30, a. ix. p. 375, a</ref> and a Cyzican.<ref>[[Athenaeus]] xiv. p. 649, f</ref> He may originally have come from Babylon, and have settled at Cyzicus. The first and third books are referred to by Athenaeus.<ref>[[Athenaeus]], ix. p. 375, f., xii. p. 515, a</ref> The time at which Agathocles lived is unknown, and his work is now lost; but it seems to have been extensively read in antiquity, as it is referred to by [[Cicero]],<ref>[[Cicero]], ''[[De Divinatione]]'' i. 24</ref> [[Pliny the Elder|Pliny]],<ref>[[Pliny the Elder]], ''[[Natural History (Pliny)|Naturalis Historia]]'' [[Method of Elenchus|elenchus]] of books iv. v. vi</ref> and other ancient writers. Agathocles also spoke of the origin of Rome.<ref>[[Sextus Pompeius Festus|Festus]] ''s. v. Romam''</ref><ref>[[Gaius Julius Solinus|Solinus]], ''Polyhistor'' 1</ref> The [[scholiast]] on [[Apollonius of Rhodes|Apollonius]]<ref>iv. 761</ref> cites Memoirs ({{lang|grc|ὑπομνήματα}}) by an Agathocles, who is usually supposed to be the same as the above-mentioned one.<ref>Compare Schol. ''ad Hes. Theog.'' 485</ref><ref>[[Stephanus of Byzantium]] ''s. v.'' {{lang|grc|Вέσβικος}}</ref><ref>''Etymol. M. s. v.'' {{lang|grc|Δίκτη}}</ref>
There are several other writers of the same name, whose works are lost to us but are mentioned by later writers: *'''Agathocles of Atrax''', who wrote a work on fishing.<ref>{{lang|grc|ἁλιευτικὰ}}, ''[[Suda]]'', 's.v.'' {{lang|grc|Κικίλιος}}</ref> *'''Agathocles of Chios''', who wrote a work on agriculture.<ref>[[Varro]], and [[Columella]], ''De Re Rustica'' i. 1</ref><ref>[[Pliny the Elder]], ''[[Natural History (Pliny)|Naturalis Historia]]'' xxii. 44</ref> *'''Agathocles of Miletus''', who wrote a work on rivers.<ref>[[Plutarch]], ''de Fluv.'' p. 1153, c</ref> *'''Agathocles of Samos''', who wrote a work on the [[constitution]] of [[Pessinus]].<ref>[[Plutarch]], ''de Fluv.'' p. 1159, a</ref>
