{{Infobox language |name=Paravilyana |nativename= |states= |region= |ethnicity= |extinct=? |ref= |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Cariban languages|Cariban]] |fam2=Pawishiana? |iso3=none |glotto=para1309 |glottorefname=Paravilhana }}
'''Paravilyana''' (Paravilhana) is an extinct and poorly attested [[Cariban language]]. Kaufman (2007) placed it in his Pawishiana branch.
